{"schema_version":1,"event":{"id":"event-f97c208014844136bbdcaa60fec41185","run_id":"run-f00e5752926f4b4087912256639027ad","sequence":26,"timestamp":"2026-07-20T21:22:29.287697Z","type":"message.created","actor":"agent","payload":{"summary":"`.next` is gitignored, no cleanup needed.\n\n## Summary\n\nCreated `app/lib/faults/` with three modules:\n\n- **`types.ts`** \u2014 `Fault` record (`customer_name`, `car_metadata {brand, model}`, `description`, `urgency`, optional `safety_advice`) plus manager-editable fields (`affected_systems`, `questions_for_customer`, `suggested_inspection_items`, `status` enum defaulting to `not_started`, `scheduled_for`). `CreateFaultInput` covers only the customer intake shape; `UpdateFaultInput` covers only manager-editable fields (including `urgency`, per the manager task's \"change priority/urgency\" requirement).\n- **`store.ts`** \u2014 module-level `Map<string, Fault>` (in-memory, no DB) with `insertFault`, `selectAllFaults`, `selectFault`, `applyFaultUpdate`. New faults get `not_started` status and empty arrays by default.\n- **`actions.ts`** \u2014 `'use server'` Server Actions `createFault`, `listFaults`, `getFault`, `updateFault` that the customer and manager screen tasks will import; mutations call `revalidatePath('/', 'layout')` since downstream route paths aren't defined yet.\n\nVerified against the actual `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` (this repo's Next 16 is not stock Next.js) for the current Server Actions/`revalidatePath` conventions, and confirmed `npm run lint` and `npm run build` both pass with no type errors, satisfying the task's completion conditions."}}}
